She is already a familiar face to viewers of Sky Sports News here in Britain. But Kate Abdo won admirers the world over when she presented the Ballon d'Or ceremony in Zurich on Monday night.

The 33-year-old broadcaster tweeted a picture of herself in rehearsals on the morning of the ceremony at the Kongresshaus in the Swiss city and was on stage as Cristiano Ronaldo was crowned the world's best player in 2014.

