Abdo, who previously worked for CNN and Sky Deutschland before joining Sky Sports in 2013, is the perfect hostess given she is fluent in English, French, German and Spanish.

She replaces the Brazilian beauty Fernanda Lima, who hosted the Ballon d'Or ceremony last year.

Ronaldo beat Lionel Messi and Manuel Neuer to the main prize, which the Portuguese star also claimed 12 months ago.

Abdo also oversaw the presentation of the awards for best coach, best goal, Fair Play award, Presidential Award and the unveiling of the FIFA FIFPro World XI for 2014.

 

